retailers saw sales growth slow last month as households reined in their spending amid an increasing squeeze on their finances .
figures compiled by the british retail consortium and kpmg showed like-for-like sales grew by 0.9 % in july , down from 1.1 % for the same month last year .
the report also marked a decline in contrast to june 's performance a month earlier when like-for-like sales rose by 1.2 % .
